-- Standard Life's profit up 12 pct on UK pensions auto-enrolment boost
-- By Richa Naidu
-- Tue Aug 05, 2014 03:26AM EDT
-- None



August 5 (Reuters) - British insurance and pensions group Standard Life Plc <SL.L> reported a 12 percent rise in first-half operating profit as more UK workers were automatically enrolled onto company pension schemes.

Standard Life said it expected to add over 300,000 new auto-enrolled customers in 2014. [ID:nRSE2323Oa] Operating profit increased to 339 million pounds ($571.7 million) in the six months ended June 30 from 304 million pounds a year earlier.